ACCORDION_QUESTION_1: What is the Ethereum Transaction Analysis App?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_1: The app provides real-time monitoring and analysis of new transactions on the Ethereum blockchain. It allows users to track and gain insights into the flow of ETH and ERC-20 tokens.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_2: What kind of analysis can I do?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_2: The app analyzes transaction details like sender, receiver, amount transferred, gas fees paid, and smart contract interactions. Users can filter data, visualize trends, and set up alerts.
ACCORDION_ANSWER_3: We run Ethereum nodes that listen for new blocks and transactions on the network. The data is then processed, enriched with relevant metadata, and stored securely.
ACCORDION_ANSWER_4: Absolutely. We do not store any personal or identifying information about our users. All transaction analysis is done on the public blockchain data.
FAQ_SUBTITLE_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: Get answers to common questions about our Ethereum transaction analysis app
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_1: Our app provides real-time analysis of new Ethereum transactions as they occur on the blockchain. It monitors the mempool, decodes transaction data, detects common contract interactions, and provides insights into transaction activities.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_2: We connect directly to Ethereum nodes to stream incoming transactions. Our system then parses the transaction data, maps it to known smart contract functions and tokens, and applies heuristics to classify the transaction activity.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_3: What kind of analysis is provided?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_3: The app identifies token transfers, DEX trades, contract deployments and interactions. It labels common DeFi activities like swapping, lending, yield farming and more. Detailed transaction summaries and labeled functions are provided.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_4: Transactions are analyzed in real-time as they enter the mempool, usually within seconds of being broadcast. Results are streamed via WebSockets for instant access to the latest data.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_5: Can I get historical transaction data?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_5: Yes, our app can also process and analyze historical transactions going back all the way to the Ethereum genesis block. Historical data can be queried via our API.
